13/01/2003
CONSTANTA, Romania -- Heavy snowstorms closed the Black Sea ports of Romania and Bulgaria on Saturday (11 January). 
Winds gusted to 75 km an hour in some areas as temperatures plunged to -10 degrees. 
Trains in both countries reported delays and ports on the Danube were closed. 
A number of villages were left without electricity and two reservoirs in southern Bulgaria reportedly overflowed. 
Late Sunday, authorities announced that the situation was improving. 
(bTV, BNT, AFP- 12/01/03)
